headline: Nancy Pelosi backs down, signals willingness to send articles of impeachment to the Senate

utterances.speaker: NEIL CAVUTO, FOX NEWS ANCHOR
utterances.sentences: So many fast-moving parts. See you live tomorrow at 10 a.m. Eastern. Here is the five.

utterances.speaker: JESSE WATTERS, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Hello, everybody. I'm Jesse Watters along with Emily Compagno, Juan Williams, Martha MacCallum, and Greg. It's 5 o'clock in New York City, and this is The Five. President Trump hitting back hard against Democrats criticizing him for taking out Iran's top general. Liberals have been smearing the president for days, claiming he was about to start World War III and that the air strike was just a big distraction from impeachment. The president responding in a big way. Take a look.

utterances.speaker: DONALD TRUMP, PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES
utterances.sentences: The radical left Democrats have expressed outrage over the termination.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.sentences: Of this horrible terrorist. We have Bernie and Nancy Pelosi, we have them all. They are all trying to say how dare you take him out that way you? You should come in and tell us what you want to do.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.sentences: You should come in and tell us so that we can call up the fake news that's back there and we can leak it. Can you imagine calling crooked Adam Schiff? He's so crooked. Say, gee, Adam, how are you doing? Listen, we have the world's number one terrorist. We'd like to set up a meeting so we can discuss his execution. Would you be willing to meet?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And in an interview with Laura Ingraham President Trump revealing brand-new information about why he ordered the air strike to kill Soleimani.

utterances.speaker: LAURA INGRAHAM, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Don't the American people have a right to know what specifically was targeted without revealing methods and sources?

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.sentences: Well, I don't think so but we will you that probably it was going to be the embassy in Baghdad.

utterances.speaker: INGRAHAM
utterances.sentences: Did you have large scale attacks planned for other embassies. And if those were planned, why can't we reveal that to the American people? Wouldn't that help your case?

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.sentences: I can reveal that I believe it would have been four embassies.

utterances.speaker: MARTHA MACCALLUM, FOX NEWS ANCHOR
utterances.sentences: Wow.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: So, Martha, imagine if President Trump doesn't give the order to take him out and then weeks later our embassies are under fire. It's like a dereliction of duty. He has to take that action.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: You know, I think that the debate that's going on is actually quite American and quite understandable in terms of people wanting to know what the intelligence was. That -- that battle for information.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Sure.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: And as Laura, you know, ask there, people it might be helpful to the president's case. And I do think that's why the president has, you know, over the past 48 hours has given a little bit more information about what he says. And he was careful there to say we believe that it could have been four embassies that were taken out. But my mind goes back to the Clinton years - -

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: -- and the assessment of the Clinton years. And I remember interviewing an FBI or overseas operative at one point who told me a story about when they had Bin Laden in their sights.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: And that, you know, there was all this back and forth between the State Department and the White House. And they had been working very hard on getting him within their scope quite literally and then were given the order to pull out. OK? So, these are decisions that only the president of the United States can make. When you are told, sir, we have a target of opportunity, we have a window to do this. And only Gina Haspel, you know, probably knows the full details about what happened there. Do you want to take the shot or not?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes. And you have to take the kill shot, right, Greg?

utterances.speaker: GREG GUTFELD, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: I don't know, I am kind of a peaceful guy, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes, you are, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I have a theory that's going to blow your mind about the media freak out --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Really?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: -- after this whole event. The Times today and right so, said that no -- there is no one president has used force less than Donald Trump since the Carter era. So, think about that. So, he is the most anti-war leader in four decades. So that explains the hysterical response that you're seeing in the media because they have to capitalize on it because it's a rare event. It doesn't happen very often. So, this is your chance to take your shot. It reminds me -- may I use an analogy -- of when once in a while, maybe once a year my wife might get a little tipsy. That is the only time I can criticize her for drinking for the whole year. So, I seize on that opportunity and say, my God, look at you. Look at you. Because she does that to me almost once a week. So, it's a -- this is the point. That Trump with this war like behavior is so rare that the media has to jump for it and scream bloody murder. And the problem that they have is they are currently living in the prism of two ideas. It's either nothing or war. Right? We do nothing or it's World War III. That's how they see it. Now if that were the case, it would be slaves or Genghis Khan. But Trump, like a sensible person, he operates in the turf between those two prisms and finds a decisive action that creates a positive outcome that is incredibly non-war-like.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And, Juan, you have to admit we are at a positive outcome right now. No U.S. casualties. It looks like there has been de-escalation and probably one of the most evil generals in our lifetime has been taken out.

utterances.speaker: JUAN WILLIAMS, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: I agree with the first thing that you said. I'm glad that we've seen de-escalation. Everything seems calm for the moment, so I'm very happy. I don't want us to go into war. But I think there are two ideas here, maybe three. Because Greg says, you know what, he is the least violent in terms of using military action of any president.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: The fact by the New York Times.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Right. But I would say this to you.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: By the way, I'm glad to hear you think so much of the times.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: David Rush.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: All right. All right. But I think that part of the reason for the concern is it seems like such an intemperate sort of off-the-cuff action. We don't know why he did it. We don't know if this is evidence of suddenly saying why not? We know that the Pentagon was shocked that he accepted that option.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: They gave him that. They offered that option.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: They gave him the option, but no -- they've offered that option to President Bush to President Obama.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And trump said yes. Don't give him the option if you don't want him to do it.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Wait, wait. Wait a minute. He's supposed to be an adult.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: There are lots of -- there are lots of options that you and I say no to every day that are good too.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: But the Pentagon gave the option.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: But here's the real point that I'd like to make. You have this very ugly situation where the president and people like Doug Collins, the congressman from Georgia go after the Democrat. You are supporting Soleimani. You think that that guy wasn't a terrorist, wasn't a bad guy. Hey, President Trump, you can have two thoughts. H's a bad guy and he was killing people. He's not up to 9/11 as Vice President Pence was charging. But he can be a bad guy. And it can be a bad idea to go out and kill him because we don't know the consequences.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: But Juan, now that we do know the consequences.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: We don't.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And the consequences at this moment has been exactly the opposite, Emily, of what the left predicted. As we heard the left predicted World War III --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: The story is not over.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: -- the left predicted World War and we're not in World War III.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: The story is not over.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: So that is the point, the left was --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Gosh. There you go.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: -- used to think the situation. And now they are afraid to --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: You are spiking the ball before you cross the line.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: No casualties, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Gosh.

utterances.speaker: EMILY COMPAGNO, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Well, I think part of this articulation of fear is exactly what that regime of terror wants us to do. Which is, refrain from responding in kind with the defensive, decisive actions for fear of more terroristic actions. Look, this isn't a new war on Iran. This is a new chapter on their on-going war against us for the last 40 years. And we, and the globe, have been bullied frankly and to treating them like a country and they're not. It's a cause. It has been a cause this entire time. They don't deserve the respect or the adherence to structure that countries do because that's not them. And you know, people argue and the Democrats have been saying this is the escalation. No, no, no. The escalation came from Iran with their steady and increased targeted attacks on us and oil production fields and the loss of American life. Exactly. We exercise restraint by not responding in kind especially after that drone attack. And you know, when you talk about the battle for information, absolutely that that should always be something -- we should always expect that our intelligence community is being forthright. But I also think the arguments have been both ways in that. Up until now the intelligence community is infallible, right? With the Mueller report? And then all of sudden why now with Iran when they should trust them to be one step ahead. All of a sudden, they've called into question and now that ascendency of escalation is all of a sudden no, no, no, it's us that escalated it?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Well, that's an interesting point. Because there is another very weird wrinkle that you are seeing in this story as the Iranians have now, I guess, accidentally we think shot down this Ukraine airliner. Here's what Democrat Congresswoman Speier had to say blaming Trump.

utterances.speaker: REP. JACKIE SPEIER (D-CA)
utterances.sentences: If what is being projected is true, this is yet another example of collateral damage from the actions that have been taken in a provocative way by the president of the United States. But for the escalation in the actions taken by Iran, there would not be 176 people dead today. It all emanate -- emanates from the killing of Soleimani.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Wow. Martha, I can't explain that one.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: I mean, I think that's really reckless talk. This was a missile that was made by Russians.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: It was sent into the sky by Iranians by all the intelligence that we have so far. And it's a huge strategy that 176 people are dead. I also just want to point out that this happened in 1988 as well and it was our fault in that situation. And Khomeini mentioned that. You know, strangely, eerily right before all of this happened. There was a missile that we took -- a missile of ours that took down a civilian plane and we claimed responsibility right after that in 1988. So, this is a tragic situation. But I think to put the blame on President Trump when it's an Iranian missile an Iranian decision to send it up is really, really, at the very least, just in really bad taste.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I mean, the story of the Middle East is the story of collateral damage.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: We've watched decades and decades and decades of innocent human suffering. Iran behind a lot of with especially with their militias and what they are doing in different countries. They've turned that region into one big game of whack a mole. To describe that we're somehow responsible to this. That is -- imagine if you had a child who was bullied every and finally punched the bully. Right? And it's somehow, it's your kid's fault. It's your kid's fault for hurting him. No, if that kid -- if that kid did something after he got beaten up, that's on him.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And it is -- it's this in the modern era of Trump derangement you have people saying the dumbest things. And it is an illness. And we are going to look back on this we are going to go -- they are going to be wondering what they were thinking. She should wonder what she's thinking.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.sentences: That missile attack does not say anything about Trump's presidency. It only speaks to Iran's incompetence. We know when their anti- aircraft radar is on and it was on during that time because it was in the midst of their missile attack on us. And they were trigger happy. They saw an aircraft that they didn't have the identity for and instead of verifying and shooting second, they shot first. It is their -- it is their bad and not us. And by the way, Soleimani used to travel on huge planes surrounded by hundreds of civilians for that collateral damage --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.sentences: -- to protect himself. And that is why our window is so --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: That's why he took the airport.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.sentences: That's why our window of availability for him was so short.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.sentences: So that collateral damage that's their process.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.sentences: That's not ours.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: The United States goes out of its way to make sure civilians are not affected. I mean, that's why terrorists they hide in churches, they hide in mosques. They hide everywhere. Schools. And we always do the best we can not to target civilians. It's the exact opposite of what the Iranians so.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Well, I think that Martha made a point. Sometimes in the course of military action that mistakes happen. Tragic mistakes. But I think you have to look at the situation this way. Jesse, we know that the administration apparently was targeting several Iranian officials. And they didn't have success in hitting some of those officials. They got Soleimani. But they didn't get the rest of them. And specific one. So, we don't know the extent of this. We still don't know the justification for what the action --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: So now you are mad they didn't get more?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You were mad that they got one.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: I didn't know. I don't know, Greg. We don't know. We, as the American people --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: But be consistent.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: -- aren't involved in a legitimate discussion of --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: -- was this justified? The consequences that are coming? I don't blame the U.S. for the shooting down of that plane. As you said, Jesse, that's the mistake made by what happened by the Iranians.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: But we should know as Americans as active citizens of this democracy why happened and why that action was taken.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes. And if you want to know more about that watch Laura Ingraham, Juan today 10 o'clock.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Eyeballs.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: The president is going to explain a lot of thinking.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Eyeballs.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: All right. Next, President Trump unleashes a blistering attack on the Democrats as he prepares for impeachment. More on that next.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: So, after weeks of waiting House Speaker Nancy Pelosi says that she does plan on sending the articles of impeachment to the Senate next week. President Trump says he is ready for a fight. Watch this.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.sentences: By the way, did you see I did nothing wrong. They even don't know what the hell is going on. In fact, it's so weak, she doesn't want to put in the articles, it's so weak. They are so pathetic. We could have them lined up, Adam. You little pencil neck.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.sentences: Nine inches. He buys the smallest shirt collar you can get, and it's loose. I said we have to have where is Hunter as a witness? I said where is Hunter. I said that's his first name. I have now made his first name where's. Where's Hunter?

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: All right. So, let's unpack that a little bit from last night. Juan, let me start with you. Just in terms of Nancy Pelosi turning over these articles of impeachment next week. Do you think that she regrets the path that she took here because this thing is, at least at this point, unless there's some surprises, sure to die in the Senate?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Yes. But I agree with you. I don't think that he is going to be convicted and removed from office. But in fact, what she did was she slowed down this process and I think there are lots of people on the Republican side who wanted this to be a quick event, quick acquittal, get it out --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: No, the Democrats wanted it to be super quick.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: Remember, they said it's such a threat of the president --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No. That was a --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: -- doing it again that that's why we can't take the time to go through the legal process for John Bolton and Mick Mulvaney.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: Well, that's what they said.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No, that's what they said because it was contrary to the White House strategy which was to slow walk this thing, get it into courts and never have come to any impeachment. So, they had -- they succeeded on three levels, Martha, here. One is they made President Trump wait and they prose attention to fall on moderate Republicans in the Senate with regard to whether or not they will support the idea of bringing people like John Bolton who had firsthand knowledge of what took place before them. And, also, I think, you know, if you saw the president last night at the rally, I don't think that he is jumping up and down and screaming about pencil neck -- how crazy. If he wasn't worried about impeachment. He doesn't like being impeached. He thinks this is a big asterisk on his presidency and a negative going into reelection.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: But in itself is an emotional strategy on the Democrat's part. We made him feel bad. We knew we won't get him out. But damn, we made him feel bad. I mean, think about that's the -- this whole thing was an emotional exercise to heal the bitter soul. I feel like a friend who gave really good advice that went ignored. I told the Democrats here on this show. I said this. You know how the movie is going to end. He's not getting impeached. His numbers are going to go up and your numbers are going to go down. And that's exactly what happened but they didn't listen. Because their emotional framework prevented them from seeing the facts. Now the Democrats are like Iran. Right? They need operation saving face to get out of a mess that that created. Right. They need the same equivalent of shooting bombs into the air into a field so that they can leave this humiliating mess with at least you know, maybe some minimal self-respect left.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: You know, Trey Gowdy was on last night with Hannity. And he was talking about how he thinks all of this, Jesse, is about flipping the Senate. That that is sort of the goal at this point to sort of threw this war of attrition and barrage of information to try to make races a lot tougher for people like Corey Gardner and Susan Collins.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Well, that failed and Juan's analysis is --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: We don't know yet. And that will be determined in the fall.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: It's dead wrong. It's dead wrong. Because if you look at the Democrats were saying, Nancy, send them over right now. Feinstein said it. Angus King said it. It was Democrats in the House and the Senate was like, hurry this thing up, guys. I don't think any moderate Republicans in the Senate felt any pressure from Nancy or the media and are worried about re-election. That might have been the strategy but that strategy has failed. During the election in nine months or whatever is going to be, impeachment is not going to be a big play.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: They are going to be talking about the economy. They are going to talk about Iran and whatever else is going to happen.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: This thing made Pelosi look weak. She said she had leverage that she never had. She said she was going to squeeze concessions and McConnell. She got no concessions. McConnell never caved. She ended up caving. She ended up holding these articles for two weeks and lost the momentum of impeachment and made herself look less powerful because she just sat there blowing in the wind. Accomplished nothing that she promised. And now this thing is just a foregone conclusion. Not one Republican is going to vote against it. In fact, two to three Senate Democrats are going to vote with Republicans.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: Well, we'll see if they can drag it into the election phase. Because I think you're right in terms of how much the American people are putting this as a priority when it comes to election time. But looking forward to the election, Emily, in terms of, you know, the where's Hunter and this the Hunter Biden stuff and the lock her up also kind of resurfaced last night. Do you that's wise?

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.sentences: Well, I think for the debates, I mean, everyone will tune in to watch it no matter this will be absolutely entertaining. And I think it's wise. It rallies his base, frankly. But Trey Gowdy he has a great point. That the strategy, first of all, it's totally transparent and obviously an impeachment won't work. But the strategy is to neuter the second term which were his language, right? So, to prevent any type of judicial appointments, the SCOTUS justice appointment. And I think the embodiment of how transparent the strategy was on the left is congressman Adam Smith yesterday, he is the twelfth-term member, he is the chair of the House Armed Services Committee and he went on CNN and was like, yes, it's time to pass along the articles of impeachment. Immediately issued a retraction. I'm sorry, I misspoke. Clearly, Pelosi called him. Get in line. The lemmings are so obvious. And that's why all the moderates that were -- that Trump is buying for, like you said, the Senate -- the Senate races aren't -- there is going to be no question whatsoever.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I just can't believe the Democrats didn't listen to Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I mean, how could they not?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes. And it's --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: Usually their bible.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And I'm here to help, Democrats.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes. Do whatever you said.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: All right. Coming up, Elizabeth Warren mocked after busting out her dance moves on the campaign trail. Plus, why she is now offering dating tips.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Welcome back. Elizabeth Warren really does have a plan for everything. The 2020 Democrat offering now of dating advice.

utterances.speaker: SEN. ELIZABETH WARREN (D-MA), PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE
utterances.sentences: Give him up. You're too good for him. If he wants to go silent, let him go. He is not the one for you. Guys who do that, you are better than that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: What did he do?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Plus, the internet mocking Senator Warren after she showed off these dance moves.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.sentences: God.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Emily, do you want to show her how to do it?

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.sentences: No. Look, you guys know how I feel like about dance shaming. Others I don't. And I actually thought right there it was cute. She was having a ball. That's awesome. Right? It's awkward but it's awesome. But the dating thing I feel like that's the whole point where what matters is being real over being down or woke or cool. And she didn't even get it right because the guy had already ghosted the girl and she was like, break up with him, honey. And it was like, no, he already did. He already ghosted her. But she doesn't know what that meant.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: OK. So, for an old man, here's my stuff, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I don't know what she's --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: She's like, I don't why he's spooking, you know, but you should get rid of him. Is that scary?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: But wait a second, Martha. Isn't she saying to the young woman, forget that guy?

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: This is so ridiculous.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: I mean, honestly, Juan, can you imagine someone asking like Dwight Eisenhower, for example, like, do you think I should break up with my boyfriend Mr. Eisenhower? I mean, General Eisenhower. I mean, it's just so ridiculous. This just started with boxers and briefs and MTV and asking Bill Clinton like why do -- why is it all so personal and touchy feely. Why do we care about the human side of this? I don't get it. I don't care. I don't know why people need a presidential candidate to be relatable and their best friend. I mean, run the country. That's what I'm concerned about. So.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Come on.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: But do you --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: No, I'm serious. Do you care about this stuff from these people?

And I think the embodiment of how transparent the strategy was on the left is congressman Adam Smith yesterday, he is the twelfth-term member, he is the chair of the House Armed Services Committee and he went on CNN and was like, yes, it's time to pass along the articles of impeachment. utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I just can't believe the Democrats didn't listen to Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. And it's --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: Usually their bible.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And I'm here to help, Democrats.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes. Do whatever you said.

utterances.utterance: All right. Coming up, Elizabeth Warren mocked after busting out her dance moves on the campaign trail. Plus, why she is now offering dating tips.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Welcome back. Elizabeth Warren really does have a plan for everything. The 2020 Democrat offering now of dating advice.

utterances.utterance: Give him up. You're too good for him. If he wants to go silent, let him go. He is not the one for you. Guys who do that, you are better than that.

utterances.utterance: What did he do?

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: God.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Emily, do you want to show her how to do it?

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: No. Look, you guys know how I feel like about dance shaming. Others I don't. And I actually thought right there it was cute. She was having a ball. That's awesome. Right? It's awkward but it's awesome. But the dating thing I feel like that's the whole point where what matters is being real over being down or woke or cool. utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK. So, for an old man, here's my stuff, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I don't know what she's --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: She's like, I don't why he's spooking, you know, but you should get rid of him. Is that scary?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But wait a second, Martha. Isn't she saying to the young woman, forget that guy?

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: This is so ridiculous.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: I mean, honestly, Juan, can you imagine someone asking like Dwight Eisenhower, for example, like, do you think I should break up with my boyfriend Mr. Eisenhower? I mean, General Eisenhower. I mean, it's just so ridiculous. This just started with boxers and briefs and MTV and asking Bill Clinton like why do -- why is it all so personal and touchy feely. Why do we care about the human side of this? I don't get it. I don't care. I don't know why people need a presidential candidate to be relatable and their best friend. I mean, run the country. That's what I'm concerned about. So.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Come on.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: But do you --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: No, I'm serious. Do you care about this stuff from these people?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, look, let me just tell you something. I'm of your school by the way but I think we're wrong. Because I think people -- it's less policy and more person. They want to have somebody they can relate to --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: Because that matter?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- to someone that they feel that guy or that woman, I feel like them.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: My God. I just want someone who runs the country and does a really good job.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: I think you're right that a lot of people care about it. I just think we need to kind of as a nation ask ourselves if we are really prioritizing the right things when we're looking at these candidates.

utterances.utterance: I think Trump has forced everybody into discovering their authenticity even if you're like Liz, and you have none. Remember her entire life is forged upon a fraud, right? Her -- she stole other people's heritage in order to get ahead. So now she's got to work backwards and figure out oh, I'll give you dating advice or I'll dance. Play songs that you can't dance to, like, what does Trump do? You Can't Always Get What You Want, right? You can't dance to it. And it's perfect. utterances.utterance: Well, Greg can't dance at all.

utterances.utterance: That's true.

utterances.utterance: Because you can't dance.

utterances.utterance: I'm such a good dancer that I keep secret.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: I think we have a little competition brewing here. I'd like to see that.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Maybe Lou Dobbs. If Lou Dobbs ask me, I will do it.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: Sixth.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Seventh.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Seventh?

utterances.utterance: I'm 13th.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You're 13th. Greg is 13th. He's like, well, you know, why am I putting my families through this? I don't need it.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Way to bring it down, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I think they showed a lot of disrespect to the Queen. And, you know, I respect the Queen a lot, and I think that she should be respected. And I think what they did was (INAUDIBLE).

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: Oh my gosh. This is so bad.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: The other thing I'd like to say is if I was born -- if I was born to a royal family like this, or if I married into a royal family like this, the last thing I would do would be leave. utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: What do you think?

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: I mean, you know, I'm going -- like I'm turning into this. I'm going back to my Elizabeth Warren theory. It's like, it doesn't really matter how you feel, right? It's all about your duty to your country. I mean, the Queen, she was a young woman when she became queen and she said, my whole life, whether it be short or long will be devoted to this country and to serving my country. All these young men serve in the military in the member -- in the royal family. And you know, so he's just walking away from all that. I can't help but think and I have absolutely zero inside information. I'm not Oprah, I don't talk to them about this, but I think he's going to regret this. I really do.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Greg, what do you think?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Here's the thing that really bugs me. Ever since Brexit, we've been adding this exit thing. Megxit sounds like a dermatological issue. I have a Megxit on my butt. utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: That's like a funny movie.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: It is.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: Greg Gutfeld becomes a member of the Royal family.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think it would be great.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: It could be the new reality show. I feel like it's a lost opportunity for them to make that monarchy, this new progressive diverse chapter. And instead, they just checked out really early. I mean, they've been there for five seconds.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.utterance: Give it a chance, for God's sake.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I have a question about Royal protocol. So if we happen to run into Harry and Meghan in the city here, in a club, or at a restaurant, do we have to then bow or curtsy?

utterances.utterance: Not you. You're not a U.K. subject.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Can we just shake hands and be like, what's up?

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: You're not a British citizen or a U.K. surrogate.

utterances.utterance: I wanted to know.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS

utterances.utterance: I said nothing like that.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: But this law is for those under 21.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That's why I think it's unfair. I mean, look, I do worry that I think it has an impact on the formation of their brain. I think they just get locked in. utterances.utterance: Well, I'll tell you right now. There's a statistics for driving right now, texting and driving accidents and fatalities are overtaking drunk driving. utterances.utterance: Yep. There you go.

utterances.utterance: All bed -- all bed --

utterances.utterance: This is --

utterances.utterance: See, that makes such a difference in your life.

utterances.utterance: I guess that wall didn't matter then.

utterances.utterance: I flew right over it.

utterances.utterance: Oh boy.

utterances.utterance: Yes, "FAN MAIL FRIDAY," answering your questions. First one, from Mary Y. Why not? What do you most hate to shop for, Martha?
